snippet.textDisplay: "they picked life over  wealth".  If you don't ever leave your house, you can't be run over by a car.  Except that people are starving to death in their homes, elders cannot leave the house for medical needs, people are committing suicides left and right, jumping out of their apartments.  I have several friends who were in quarantine for over 45 days in Shanghai, and were lucky to be able to leave the country because they were foreigners.  One of them had to ride a bike to the airport since nobody would be able to drive her, and she had to sleep at the airport for 2 days to wait for her negative lab results before allowed to get on the plane to leave.
